Citation.sAbstract: The liquid saturated properties (solubility, density, and viscosity) data for the binary system of ethane + n-tetradecane at three temperatures (323, 373, and 423) K were measured using a designed pressure volume temperature (PVT) apparatus. The saturated liquid phase properties were measured for pressures up to 8 MPa. The experimental data (saturated liquid phase composition and density) were compared with the modeling results obtained using the Peng Robinson and Soave Redlich Kwong equations of state.
Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Modeling of Liquid Saturated Properties (Solubility, Density, and Viscosity) of (Ethane + n-Tetradecane) Binary Systems
